The Canton of Bourganeuf is a canton situated in the Creuse dpartement and in the Limousin region of central France.

== Geography ==
An area of farming and forestry in the arrondissement of Guret, centred on the town of Bourganeuf. The altitude varies from 271m (Saint-Martin-Sainte-Catherine) to 721m (Soubrebost) with an average altitude of 452m.

== Population ==

